Convicted forex trader Jabulani “Cashflow” Ngcobo is going to be a father. Ngcobo and his fabulous wife Tumi Links are expecting a baby, a year after they got engaged in glamourous style. Links is a model, as well as an influencer. The news about the pregnancy came after the couple threw a lavish baby shower at the swanky West Cliff Hotel, where A-listers including Connie Ferguson, Lasizwe, Ayanda Cwane, Sophie Ndaba, and Shauwn “Mamkhize” Mkhize attended. Ngcobo, who made his fortune on forex trading, is said to be over the moon and cannot wait to meet his bundle of joy. “Already he is shopping up a storm. The baby room is ready and he has bought designer baby clothes and other goodies,” said a source. Another source added that Ngcobo had been telling friends that he cannot wait to help with changing nappies and feeding the baby, which is expected to arrived in June.       Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.